# 🔹 Structures

A structure stores different data types together.

Example:

```c
struct Student
{
   int id;
   char name[20];
   float marks;
};
```

---

## Structure Variable

```c
struct Student s1;
```

---

## Accessing Members

```c
s1.id = 1;
```

using dot operator:

```c
.
```

---

## Structure Pointer

```c
struct Student *p;
```

Access using:

```c
p->id
```

📌 GATE Favorite.

---

# 🔹 Structures vs Arrays

| Structure       | Array     |
| --------------- | --------- |
| Different types | Same type |
| User-defined    | Built-in  |

---

# 🔹 Union

Union allows multiple members to share same memory.

Example:

```c
union Data
{
   int i;
   float f;
   char ch;
};
```

---

## Important Property

Memory allocated = size of largest member.

Example:

```c
union U
{
   int i;
   double d;
};
```

Size = size(double)

📌 Very common GATE question.

---

# 🔹 Structure vs Union

| Structure           | Union                |
| ------------------- | -------------------- |
| Separate memory     | Shared memory        |
| Larger size         | Smaller size         |
| Simultaneous access | One member at a time |

---

# 🔹 Dynamic Memory Allocation (DMA)

Memory allocated during runtime.

Header:

```c
#include <stdlib.h>
```

---

# 🔹 malloc()

Allocates memory.

```c
int *p;

p=(int*)malloc(5*sizeof(int));
```

---

## Characteristics

* Uninitialized memory
* Returns void pointer

---

# 🔹 calloc()

Allocates and initializes memory to zero.

```c
p=(int*)calloc(5,sizeof(int));
```

---

# 🔹 realloc()

Changes memory size.

```c
p=realloc(p,new_size);
```

---

# 🔹 free()

Releases memory.

```c
free(p);
```

Important to avoid memory leaks.

---

# 🔹 Memory Leak

Occurs when allocated memory is not freed.

Example:

```c
malloc(...)
```

without

```c
free(...)
```

📌 Common interview & GATE concept.

---

# 🔹 Common GATE Traps

### Trap 1

```c
strlen()
```

does NOT count '\0'.

---

### Trap 2

Union size = largest member size.

---

### Trap 3

```c
malloc()
```

does NOT initialize memory.

---

### Trap 4

Access structure pointer using:

```c
->
```

not dot operator.

